Fresh Pi session: BUILD THE CANON TDD TEST LIST.

Inputs:
- User prompt: {{run.dir}}/prompt/prompt.md
- Approved use case: find the latest {{run.dir}}/use-case/use-case-*.md
- Repository root: {{inputs.repo-root}}
- Revision issues, if any: {{run.issues-file}}

Goal:
List behavioral test scenarios before writing any concrete test code.

Rules:
- Inspect existing tests and behavior as needed, but do not edit repository files.
- Cover the main success flow, important alternatives/errors, boundaries, and relevant behavior that must not regress.
- Keep the list minimal and non-overlapping: each scenario must add one independently observable rule, not restate a broader scenario or split normal/strict modes into duplicate increments.
- A pending scenario must be capable of producing meaningful red against current behavior. Put already-working controls and general regression expectations in a change-detecting scenario's acceptance details or the broad validation plan, not in separate pending scenarios.
- Keep scenarios behavioral: invocation context plus observable expected result.
- Do not choose implementation, test framework details, files, classes, mocks, or internal architecture.
- Do not turn scenarios into test code.
- Give every scenario a stable id such as SC-001 and initial state `pending`.
- Prefer a focused list; do not invent scope outside the approved use case.

Write:
- Machine-readable list: {{run.dir}}/test-list/scenarios-initial.json
- Human-readable list: {{run.dir}}/test-list/scenarios-initial.md
- Status: {{run.dir}}/test-list/build-status-{{run.round}}.json

JSON shape:
{"version":1,"scenarios":[{"id":"SC-001","description":"...","expected_behavior":"...","source":"main-success-3","state":"pending"}]}

Status examples:
{"status":"pass","summary":"behavioral test list ready","issues_file":null}
{"status":"fail","summary":"test list needs revision","issues_file":null}
